The Chronicle Oliver Kazunga, Senior Business Reporter THE Reserve Bank of Zimbabwe’s Monetary Policy Committee (MPC) has approved a $500 million loan facility for term financing to the Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises at 30 percent interest per annum. At its latest meeting held on 30 April 2021 in support of the economic activity and the prevailing macro-economic stability, the MPC also resolved to maintain the bank policy rate at 40 percent and the interest rate on the Medium-Term Accommodation Facility (MBA) at 30 percent per annum. The Reserve Bank also reaffirmed its position to support bureau de change with foreign exchange requirements to support MSMEs, which need foreign currency for their various productive requirements. In a post-meting statement, the RBZ said the MPC has reaffirmed its strong commitment to continue with the conservative monetary policy stance to ensure the prevailing price stability is maintained. “The MPC approved a facility of ZW$500 million for term finance for Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises (MSMEs), which the MSMEs will access from banks and microfinance institutions at 30 percent per annum for purposes of enhancing production and productivity across all the sectors of the economy,” it said. The MPC has also expressed confidence that the prevailing slowdown in inflation is likely to continue with a forecast of 55 percent by July this year. – @okazunga 